injuries.longComment: Christiansen suffered a hamstring injury during the Chiefs' Week 4 win over New York and has since been placed on the practice squad IR. The 26-year-old was elevated to Kansas City's active roster for two games this year, playing on 45 percent of the team's special teams snaps.
injuries.shortComment: Christiansen (hamstring) was placed on the practice squad injured list Saturday, Aaron Wilson of KPRC 2 Houston reports.

injuries.longComment: Fortson suffered the injury during practice in late July. It's still unclear what the specific issue is, but head coach Andy Reid said the Valdosta State product would be getting his shoulder "done." He'll now miss the 2023 season unless he reaches an injury settlement with the team and is able to get back to full health before the season comes to an end.
injuries.shortComment: Fortson (shoulder) was placed on injured reserve Tuesday, Matt Derrick of ChiefsDigest.com reports.

injuries.longComment: James failed to log a practice all week while dealing with an MCL injury. He played in just three offensive snaps in Week 2 against the Jaguars but plays an important role as the Chiefs' primary returner on special teams. He'll be forced to sit out for at least the next four games and is eligible to return in Week 7 against the Chargers on Sunday, Oct. 22.
injuries.shortComment: The Chiefs placed James (knee) on injured reserve Saturday, Aaron Wilson of KPRC 2 Houston reports.

injuries.longComment: Johnson's injury details are unknown, but the second-year-pro will be sidelined until he has recovered. Selected in the seventh round of the 2022 Draft, Johnson appeared only on special teams during his rookie season. Once recovered, Johnson will continue to work to earn a role in Kansas City's secondary.
injuries.shortComment: Johnson (knee) did not participate in practice Sunday, Pete Sweeney of ArrowheadPride.com reports.

injuries.longComment: The wideout was unclaimed after being waived/injured Tuesday, meaning he's been reverted to IR. Remigio went undrafted this past year out of Fresno State, where he recorded 852 receiving yards in his final year of college.
injuries.shortComment: Remigio (wrist) reverted to Kansas City's reserve/injured list Wednesday, Matt Derrick of ChiefsDigest.com reports.

injuries.longComment: Tega Wanogho suffered the injury during Sunday's win against Chicago and will now miss the team's next four games at minimum. He'll be eligible to return in Week 8 against the Broncos, although it's not clear if he will need more time than that to recover.
injuries.shortComment: Tega Wanogho (quadriceps) was placed on IR on Wednesday, Matt McMullen of the Chiefs' official site reports.

injuries.longComment: Watson dislocated his elbow in Thursday's 19-8 win over the Broncos. The MRI revealed positive news for the wide receiver, but Watson may still miss some game action. His participation level in practice when the Chiefs begin preparing to face the Chargers will provide clarity regarding Watson's chances of suiting up Week 7.
injuries.shortComment: Watson hasn't been ruled out for Kansas City's Week 7 game against the Chargers after an MRI revealed no structural damage, but his dislocated elbow could still keep him out for a few weeks, Jeremy Fowler of ESPN reports.
